A 91-year-old man has been charged with murdering his 92-year-old wife. Avon and Somerset Police said Anne Woodbridge was found dead at a residential address in Weston-super-Mare on Monday morning. Her husband, John Woodbridge, of Ashcombe Road, Weston-super-Mare, has since been charged with her murder. A force spokesman said Woodbridge had been due to appear before Bristol Magistrates’ Court on Thursday. This is a breaking news story, more to follow soon… Check back shortly for further updates. Got a story? Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. Or you can submit your videos and pictures here. For more stories like this, check our news page. Follow Metro.co.uk on Twitter and Facebook for the latest news updates. You can now also get Metro.co.uk articles sent straight to your device. Sign up for our daily push alerts here.